title: For Sale:  CZ27 Pistole
postcontent:
The vz. 27 is a Czech semi-automatic pistol, based on the pistole vz. 24, and chambered for 7.65 mm Browning/.32 ACP. It is often designated the CZ 27 after the naming scheme used by the Česká zbrojovka factory for post-World War II commercial products. However, it is correctly known as vz. 27, an abbreviation of the Czech "vzor 27", or "Model 27".
After the German occupation of Czechoslovakia in 1938 the pistol was folded into the German armed and police forces as the P27. Construction of the pistol continued in
Czechoslovakia until the 1950s. Allegedly, the Czech military sold five and a half thousand surplus vz. 27s to the Swiss in 1973 for half a million marks. Between 620,000 and 650,000 were manufactured in total, 452,500 of those under German occupation. In December of 1948, a gift of five "ČZ 247" automatic variants of the pistol (based on both the vz. 24 and vz. 27) was sent to Ethiopian ruler Haile Selassie. In 1949, the vz. pistol was exported to 28 countries, including Turkey (3,286 pistols), England, South Africa, Egypt, Kenya, and Pakistan.

title: For Sale:  SCAM ALERT!!!!!!
postcontent:
Check cashing scam. If you receive a response wanting to buy your firearm from a malinabobb​y1234, or Menzies Caviness it is a scam. They will say they cant speak on the phone due to health reasons. they will "accidentally" mail you a check for several thousands more than you are asking. Then they will text you in a panic asking you to mail the balance back after you cash the check. They have a sob story about a sick daughter to go with it.
The check is mailed from a nonexistent business in GA, from a nonexistent address. they will ask that you mail the funds to their daughters doctor in China...

This process is done my melting small devotes, holes , lines etc.. In the polymer this caused the edges of the holes,lines devotes to be raised giving texture.

This is a permanent alternative to grip tape or the grips that slide over the handle. Grip tape eventually wears down and can be an hassle to remove and install new grip tape. It also isn't very eye appealing on some guns especially on FDE or OD green guns at least in our opinion.

postcontent:
This is a Lone Wolf long 6" conversion barrel for the Glock G20 which allows you to fire .40 S&W rounds instead of 10mm Auto rounds. The barrel is in great condition with less than 50 rounds fired total, and it is in essentially perfect condition. It is a drop in barrel which will fit any G20 model including SF and Gen. 4 versions. The barrel is 6" long so it does extend past the end of the slide about an inch, however this will create a slight increase in the bullet velocity. The .40 S&W rounds will fit in the G20 10mm Auto magazines without a problem. This will allow you to practice with your G20 without having to go through tons of expensive and often hard to find 10mm Auto ammunition. It will also give you added peace of mind knowing that if 10mm Auto ammunition ever becomes EXTREMELY DIFFICULT to find you will still be able to use your G20 with the much more common .40 S&W round. The barrel also has standard rifling so you can use lead ammunition without the issues that the Glock hexagonal rifling can cause. These barrels are sold by Lone Wolf online for $125 new, so I am offering mine for $75. However it is almost in exactly the same condition as the new ones you would get from Lone Wolf.

title: For Sale:  Lee-Enfield No. 1 MK III SMLE .303 British
postcontent:
Want to sell my Lee-Enfield No. 1 MK III, manufactured at the Ishapore Arsenal in India in the 1920s. In original condition, and retains the magazine cut-off and round knob-type cocking piece.

The stock disc is marked with sanskrit characters, which would be consistent with a rifle issued to an Indian regiment. If you really did some digging you could probably determine exactly what unit the rifle was assigned to.

The bore appears somewhat dark, but the rifling is sharp and I think a thorough cleaning would brighten it up nicely. Action is smooth and mechanically sound. It has the standard 10-round detachable magazine.

The metal is in excellent condition with no pitting and comparatively minor finish loss. Finish is the dark black almost paintlike appearance typical of the Ishapore Arsenal. Numerous proofing marks and UK property stamps are visible and picked out in white. A
couple of arsenal-level repairs are visible on the buttstock. 

Meet FTF in the NoVA area, ID required. I can also make some .303 ammo available to the buyer. Additional pictures also available.

title: For Sale:  Registering on Armslist
location: NY and all of U.S., Rochester, New York
postcontent: You can not expect Armslist to require everyone to register in order to buy or sell items on Armslist.  Scams can happen anywhere to anyone, but if people would use good judgement and not be so eager to buy these items out of desperation in fear that they might not have another chance then only a very small fraction of these scammers would actually succeed !  Remember if something seems too good to be true . . . IT PROBABLY IS.  Don't take chances, don't send items or money in good faith, meet in person when ever possible and if you decide to do transactions through the mail only send or accept money via paypal. ANYONE can sign up and use paypal, which will protect you from scams and in the event you are scammed, will enable you to take action against that person.  Be smart, protect yourself and your hard earned money !
